This is the open source community version of Paperpile, a reference manager for the desktop and the web.  

Paperpile is built on web-technologies, in particular Catalyst (catalystwebframework.org) and Titanium (appcelerator.com). At the moment, only Linux is supported but versions for OS X and Windows will follow soon. 

Please visit paperpile.com for news on the product and code.paperpile.org for information on Paperpile development. 

To build Paperpile from the source follow these steps (use linux32 or linux64 depending on your architecture):

1. Checkout Paperpile:

# git clone git@github.com:wash/paperpile.git

2. Download Titanium runtime (optional)Â¶

# cd build
# ./perl.pl build.pl get_titanium

3. Run Paperpile

Titanium (standalone) version:

# titanium/linux32/paperpile

Via web-browser:

# cd catalyst/script
# ./start_linux32

Open Paperpile on 127.0.0.1:3000

For officially supported packages visit paperpile.com.

